    "created_at": "2014-06-08T06:36:57Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-06-08T06:36:57Z",
    "body": "Note that we are very intentionally still using segmented stacks because we would like the ability to run library code when a task overflows the stack. This is precisely to print that the stack has overflowed, as well as leaving the door open in the future to do something more flavorful.\n\nWe would need to figure out how to catch SIGSEGV and print a message or explicitly decide to not have this feature before moving forward with this issue.\n",
