    "created_at": "2014-07-27T08:50:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-27T08:51:06Z",
    "body": "@retep998: LLVM can't really support recovering from a stack overflow. The best it can do is allow you to block the thread forever, because it would be undefined behaviour to unwind from a location it didn't consider as possibly unwinding. It's also impossible to write low-level Rust code that's correct in the presence of unwinding from any function prelude.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
